docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, Sept. 15 -- George M. Humphrey, Secretary of the Treasury, warned today that the United States Government henceforth was going to take a hard look at any proposal to spend public funds for competitive enterprises abroad.

docs.snippet: During the past week the foreign exchange market passed through a period of extreme irregularity. The British pound sterling moved back and forth never seeming able to steady itself while the Canadian dollar displayed a very strong undertone....
docs.lead_paragraph: During the past week the foreign exchange market passed through a period of extreme irregularity. The British pound sterling moved back and forth never seeming able to steady itself while the Canadian dollar displayed a very strong undertone. Business was reported to have picked up considerably over the previous week.
